## PHASE VF-1 — Color Token Correction

**Goal:** Brand colors are locked to Photoshop samples in `reference-images/Initial Build and Client Identity/` (`jjbbq-red.png`, `jjbbq-yellow.png`, `jjbbq-pink-light.png`, `jjbbq-pink-dark.png`). Black `#000000` and white `#ffffff` are standard.

**Cursor Prompt:**

Open `assets/scss/_variables.scss`.

Use these official values (RGB shown for documentation):

```scss
// PRIMARY RED — jjbbq-red.png · rgb(221, 44, 47)
$color-red: #dd2c2f;

// GOLD / YELLOW — jjbbq-yellow.png · rgb(247, 177, 18)
$color-gold: #f7b112;
$color-gold-dark: #bb8306; // darker gold derived from official swatch (hover / depth)

// PINKS — jjbbq-pink-light.png · rgb(250, 150, 141) · jjbbq-pink-dark.png · rgb(251, 77, 81)
$color-pink-light: #fa968d;
$color-pink-dark: #fb4d51;

$color-black: #000000;
$color-white: #ffffff;

// UI neutrals (supporting — adjust only if contrast testing requires)
$color-cream: #faf6f0;
$color-dark-bg: #1a0000;
$color-text-on-red: #fff5e0;
```

Expose `--color-pink-light`, `--color-pink-dark`, and keep `--color-pink` as an alias for `--color-pink-light` if older partials expect it.

After updating tokens, compile SCSS and verify:
- Hero / header use `$color-red` (`#dd2c2f`)
- Gold band / gold accents use `$color-gold` (`#f7b112`)
- No stray legacy hex (`#CC0000`, `#F5A800`, etc.) in SCSS

Do not change layout or structural CSS in this phase — tokens only.

