## PHASE VF-3 — Secondary Pig Butt Asset Placement

**Goal:** The secondary "pig butt" circular mark (reference-images/logo-butt.png) is unused. It should be deployed as a decorative watermark element in at least two locations: the hero background and the footer.

**Cursor Prompt:**

The secondary logo asset lives at `reference-images/logo-butt.png`. This is the standalone circular pig rear illustration — used as a decorative accent, not a navigational element.

Make the following two placements:

**1. Hero background watermark:**
In the hero section CSS, add the pig butt as a background image positioned to the far right, partially cropped, at low opacity. This creates depth without competing with the main logo:

```scss
.hero {
  position: relative;
  overflow: hidden;

  &::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    right: -60px;
    bottom: -40px;
    width: 380px;
    height: 380px;
    background-image: url('../../reference-images/logo-butt.png');
    background-size: contain;
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    opacity: 0.08;
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 0;
  }
}

// Ensure hero content sits above the watermark
.hero__content {
  position: relative;
  z-index: 1;
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .hero::after {
    width: 220px;
    height: 220px;
    right: -30px;
    bottom: -20px;
  }
}
```

**2. Footer watermark:**
Apply the same technique to the footer, positioned left side, slightly larger opacity since the footer is dark:

```scss
.site-footer {
  position: relative;
  overflow: hidden;

  &::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: -80px;
    top: 50%;
    transform: translateY(-50%);
    width: 300px;
    height: 300px;
    background-image: url('../../reference-images/logo-butt.png');
    background-size: contain;
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    opacity: 0.06;
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 0;
  }
}

.site-footer__inner {
  position: relative;
  z-index: 1;
}
```

Verify the watermarks do not affect click targets, tab order, or layout reflow.

