## PHASE VF-4 — Typography Upgrade

**Goal:** The current font choices feel generic and don't match the cartoon-bold personality of the logo lettering. Headline fonts should push toward chunky, characterful, hand-drawn energy. Body copy should remain clean and readable.

**Cursor Prompt:**

Open `functions.php` (or wherever Google Fonts are enqueued) and `assets/scss/_typography.scss`.

**1. Replace the current headline font enqueue with:**
```php
// In functions.php wp_enqueue_style call:
'https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Boogaloo&family=Nunito:wght@400;600;700&display=swap'
```

- `Boogaloo` — headline font. Chunky, rounded, cartoon energy. Matches the logo's personality without being a direct copy.
- `Nunito` — body font. Rounded, friendly, highly readable at small sizes.

**2. Update SCSS font variables:**
```scss
$font-display: 'Boogaloo', cursive;
$font-body:    'Nunito', sans-serif;
```

**3. Update headline usage across the theme:**
```scss
h1, h2, h3,
.section-title,
.hero__headline,
.card__title,
.nav__logo-text {
  font-family: $font-display;
  letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  line-height: 1.1;
}

body, p, li, td, input, textarea, select {
  font-family: $font-body;
}
```

**4. Scale the hero headline up.** With Boogaloo loaded, bump the hero `<h1>` to `clamp(2.4rem, 6vw, 4.2rem)` so it commands the space without being crammed.

Do not change font colors, section backgrounds, or layout in this phase.

