## PHASE VF-5 — Menu Card Visual Upgrade

**Goal:** The homepage menu preview cards are plain white boxes with thin borders. They need more brand energy — a strong left-border accent, bolder price display, and a subtle warmth to the background.

**Cursor Prompt:**

Open the styles for the menu preview cards. These are likely in `assets/scss/_menu.scss` or `_home.scss`.

Apply the following updates:

```scss
.menu-card {
  background-color: $color-cream;         // Warm off-white, not pure white
  border: 2px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
  border-left: 5px solid $color-red;      // Bold red left-border accent
  border-radius: 4px;
  padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
  transition: transform 0.15s ease, box-shadow 0.15s ease;

  &:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: 0 6px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12);
  }
}

.menu-card__name {
  font-family: $font-display;
  font-size: 1.05rem;
  color: $color-black;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.02em;
}

.menu-card__price {
  font-family: $font-display;
  font-size: 1.15rem;
  color: $color-red;
  font-weight: 700;
  white-space: nowrap;
  margin-left: 1rem;
}

// Description line (shown on full menu page, hidden on homepage preview)
.menu-card__desc {
  font-family: $font-body;
  font-size: 0.85rem;
  color: #555;
  margin-top: 0.25rem;
}
```

Also verify the "Full Menu" button below the cards uses `$color-red` as background with `$color-gold` or white text — it should not be a ghost/outline button on this section.

