## PHASE VF-6 — Next Pop-Up Card Refinement

**Goal:** The Next Pop-Up event card on the gold section is structurally strong but the card border and internal typography need polish. The date should read as the hero of the card, not just another line.

**Cursor Prompt:**

Open the styles for the upcoming event card. Likely in `assets/scss/_events.scss` or `_home.scss`.

Update the event card:

```scss
.event-card--upcoming {
  background: #FFFFFF;
  border: 3px solid $color-black;
  border-radius: 6px;
  box-shadow: 6px 6px 0px $color-black;  // Hard offset shadow — retro/bold feel
  padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
  max-width: 480px;
  margin: 0 auto;
}

.event-card__date {
  font-family: $font-display;
  font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 4vw, 2rem);
  color: $color-red;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.03em;
  line-height: 1;
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
}

.event-card__venue {
  font-family: $font-display;
  font-size: 1.2rem;
  color: $color-black;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
}

.event-card__address,
.event-card__time {
  font-family: $font-body;
  font-size: 0.9rem;
  color: #444;
  line-height: 1.5;
}
```

The hard-offset box shadow (`6px 6px 0px #000`) echoes the black outline style of the logo lettering and gives the card a bold, hand-stamped quality that fits the brand.

