## PHASE VF-8 — QA & Visual Regression Check

**Goal:** Confirm all visual fix phases rendered correctly, no regressions in layout or accessibility, and the site reads as a cohesive brand expression.

**Cursor Prompt:**

Perform a full visual and code QA pass across all pages. Check the following items and note any failures:

**Color:**
- [ ] Hero background uses official red (`#dd2c2f` · rgb 221, 44, 47)
- [ ] Gold/Next Pop-Up section uses official gold (`#f7b112` · rgb 247, 177, 18)
- [ ] Pink tokens available: light `#fa968d`, dark `#fb4d51` (per `jjbbq-pink-*.png`)
- [ ] No legacy brand hex (`#CC0000`, `#F5A800`, etc.) in SCSS
- [ ] Menu card left-border accent uses `--color-red`

**Logo & Assets:**
- [ ] Primary logo appears in hero, centered, with drop shadow
- [ ] Pig butt watermark visible (low opacity) in hero and footer
- [ ] Footer shows logo image, not text-only wordmark
- [ ] No broken image `alt` text showing in place of images

**Typography:**
- [ ] Boogaloo loaded and applied to all headings and section titles
- [ ] Nunito loaded and applied to all body copy
- [ ] Hero headline is `clamp(2.4rem, 6vw, 4.2rem)` or similar — not undersized
- [ ] No fallback to Arial, Inter, or system-ui for display text

**Cards & Components:**
- [ ] Menu cards show red left-border, warm cream background, no pure white
- [ ] Event card has hard-offset box shadow
- [ ] "Full Menu" CTA is a solid red button, not ghost/outline

**Accessibility:**
- [ ] Logo images have descriptive `alt` attributes
- [ ] Watermark pseudo-elements have `pointer-events: none`
- [ ] Color contrast on gold section passes WCAG AA (black text on `#f7b112` — verify after deploy)
- [ ] Instagram link has `aria-label`

If any item fails, fix before marking VF phases complete.
